<subSubSection id="5D420FAE285908BD17EF0DD058424EDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="53F69C1D31A55AE68D8A20B5CF964112" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="921DE5E3299C23B376DAA1DD058987A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.6-2.9 mm long (mean = 2.66 mm; n = 5); 2.48-2.64
<normalizedToken id="2FFB5407AEE4B6CF6105DF421D8F0542" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the protibiae posterior faces flat, unarmed; antennal club as broad as tall; posterolateral carina oblique, granulate; elytral disc flat, without a transverse depression; elytral striae deeply impressed on disc; elytral interstriae with at least two rows of tubercles and long erect fine hair-like setae, setae 2
<normalizedToken id="B5D9CB368E7190BC995297F8D8B092C3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
width of an interstria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
